              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Nvidia’s AI chip limits spark backlash</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-16-1.png" alt="Nvidia’s AI chip limits spark backlash" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The US’s new AI chip export rules have <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-16-01-2025-h1-1-rattled-allies" target="_blank">rattled allies</a> like Poland and Israel. Poland’s Deputy PM called the decision “incomprehensible,” while Israeli officials warn the restrictions could stifle their AI advancements. The new measures split countries into tiers, with close allies facing minimal restrictions and others limited in purchasing advanced chips. Companies like Nvidia and Oracle say these rules could hurt the US tech industry. AI development remains a key focus for countries like Israel, where technology accounts for 20% of GDP. Poland, meanwhile, is becoming a hub for IT services.</p>
        </mj-text>
