              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Bond rally fuels rate cut speculation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">US government bonds surged as <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-16-01-2025-h2-2-softer-inflation-data" target="_blank">softer inflation data</a> reignited hopes for Fed rate cuts. Yields on five- and 10-year Treasuries fell sharply. The 10-year yield dropped 14 basis points to 4.65%, marking its biggest daily decline since August. Traders now fully price in a rate cut by July. December’s core CPI rose just 0.2%, boosting market confidence in further Fed easing. Treasury gains also lifted global bond markets, particularly in the UK and eurozone.</p>
        </mj-text>
